.TH H_SHELL 1

.SH NAME
hsh \- runs the hsh shell

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B ./hsh
to launch the shell in interactive mode

.SH DESCRIPTION
hsh is a shell-like program (similar to zsh or bash) that can run user commands, it will create a list from PATH and attempt to search those directories for the selected commands, alternatively supplying the path in the command i.e:
.PP
.nf
.RS
/bin/ls
.RE
.fi
.PP

Will have the shell search
.B /bin/
for
.B ls

.SH OPTIONS
.B ./hsh
can be run in non-interactive mode, which can be done by making the command like the example below:
.PP
.nf
.RS
echo "ls /var" | ./hsh
.RE
.fi
.PP

.SH BUGS
certain commands like
.B cd
currently do not work

.SH AUTHORS
.nf
Max Brook (12107@holbertonstudents.com)
Matthew Wirski (12106@holbertonstudents.com)
.fi

